VSri Chandrasekharendra Sangeeta Educational Society presented a vocal recital by  G. Srinivasa Raghavan, a septuagenarian sponsored by Sri Maharajapuram Santanam Trust. Srinivasa was accompanied by Dinakar on the violin, Burra Sriram on mridangam and T.P.Balasubramanyam on the ghatam. Srinivasa presented a neat and devoted concert featuring Tamil compositions and noted items of the great Late Maharajapuram Santanam. He began his recital with avarnamin Simhendra Madyam.Vinayaka ninu vinain Hamsadwani with neatswaramwas rendered.Rara maintidakain Asaveri was neatly rendered. Pantuvarali was taken for an elaborated expansion forEnnaganu Ramabhajanof Ramadasu with impressiveneravalandswaram.Natakuranji was neatly briefed forParvathi kumaramwhich was very appealing. Surati was taken for a detailed expansion in which he sang Deekshitar&#8217;sAngaraka masryamaNavagraha kriti.Kamalamba na chinta theercha vayyain Kannada was soothing.Sankerabharanamwas the main attraction and theragamwas rendered withraga bhavamin a traditional way and Sri Sankeracharyam was sung with detailedswaramand the effort was good. The violin by Dinakar added lustre to the concert. The percussion duo did their jobs respectively well. Thetaniin Aditalamwas good.Sri Chakra Raja Simhasaneshwari,a noted piece of Santanam was sung in a Raga Malika.On the whole the concert was rich in tradition but lackedsahityaclarity.
